Chilean Stocks: Colbun, La Polar and Ripley Drop; Endesa Rises

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-10-18T14:20:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/chilean-stocks-colbun-la-polar-and-ripley-drop-endesa-rises.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:54 a.m. in Santiago.  The Ipsa index fell 0.2 percent to 4,002.24. The  MSCI Chile (MXCL) 
index slid 2.1 percent to 2,204.19.  Colbun SA (COLBUN)   retreated 0.5 percent to 125.5 pesos
and earlier lost 3.3 percent. Chile’s second-largest power
generator by market value was dropped by local brokerage firm IM
Trust SA from its portfolio of 10 favorite Chilean stocks and
replaced by Empresa Nacional de Electricidad SA, or Endesa,
(ENDESA CC), the country’s largest generator.  Endesa rose 0.8 percent to 739.7 pesos.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   fell 1.2 percent to 405
pesos and earlier retreated 6.5 percent, its third day of
losses. The department store operator, which is seeking to avert
its second bankruptcy in 12 years, had a net loss of 506 billion
pesos ($987 million) in the first seven months of the year,
Diario Financiero reported, citing documents elaborated by the
Chilean retailer’s trustee Herman Chadwick.  Ripley Corp SA (RIPLEY)   dropped 1.5 percent to 436
pesos, its lowest price in a week. Chile’s third largest
department store operator had its recommendation cut to
“underweight” from “overweight” at the brokerage unit of
local lender Banco de Credito & Inversiones.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  